The fourth edition of the Bayelsa Governor’s Football Tournament christened ‘The Prosperity Cup’ will kick off on Monday, May 2, 2022, at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex, Yenagoa. The defending champions, Okolobiri community now known as Gbarain Selected Stars FC will trade tackles with newcomers Bayelsa Medical University (BMU) at the curtain-raiser. A statement issued on Sunday by the organisers’ media officer, Patrick Ndubuisi, said that over 200 teams registered for the 2022 edition and will compete for the coveted trophy and the prize money. It said the state Governor, Douye Diri, will perform the ceremonial kick-off as the special guest of honour while the deputy governor, Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, is the guest of honour. The Commissioner for Youth and Sports Development, Daniel Igali, will be the chief host. Also expected to be in attendance at the opening ceremony are members of the state executive council, the state House of Assembly, council chairmen, and sports stakeholders, among others. The statement urged members of the public and football enthusiasts, in particular, to turn out en mass and get entertained by grassroots football talents.